31:17.726 --> 31:19.059
while he was alive.

31:20.195 --> 31:21.561
A lot of things you're saying
make me think

31:21.563 --> 31:23.397
of one of the earliest owners
of your property.

31:23.399 --> 31:24.798
His name was
Captain Martin Williams

31:24.800 --> 31:27.067
and he was born in town
back in 1838.

31:27.069 --> 31:29.736
So you said he caused a lot
of deaths while he was alive.

31:29.738 --> 31:31.672
Well, Williams did fight
for the Confederacy

31:31.674 --> 31:33.740
during the Civil War.

31:33.742 --> 31:36.009
Safe to say he had his
hand in a lot of deaths.

31:36.011 --> 31:37.744
When he came home
after the war,

31:37.746 --> 31:39.479
he became a wealthy farmer
and merchant,

31:39.481 --> 31:41.281
but the killing
didn't stop.

31:41.283 --> 31:45.218
Williams actually murdered a man
in town in 1894.

31:45.220 --> 31:46.919
This is how it went down.

31:46.921 --> 31:49.856
The Captain's son was
insulted by a black guy.

31:49.858 --> 31:51.557
So Captain William
took it upon himself

31:51.559 --> 31:54.161
to take a rifle
and go look for the guy.

31:55.297 --> 31:58.097
He comes across
the black guy's father,

31:58.099 --> 32:02.168
and he basically demands
that he takes him to his son.

32:02.170 --> 32:05.171
So like any father would do,
he refused.

32:05.173 --> 32:07.373
Williams freaked out
